I've come for the one I love.

24:52.800 --> 24:55.600
I made the mistake of
letting you go once.

24:55.633 --> 24:57.533
I'm done making mistakes.

25:03.700 --> 25:05.400
[SCREAMING]

25:07.133 --> 25:09.367
You can't forget me, Ben.

25:09.400 --> 25:11.733
You can't forget me!

25:51.533 --> 25:55.233
That's not funny at all.
That's....

25:55.267 --> 25:57.267
[MAN SPEAKING SPANISH ON TV]

25:58.533 --> 26:04.100
...Spanish...
I can understand you, and you...

26:12.400 --> 26:16.067
...and you, and you.

26:21.100 --> 26:22.433
[MOANING]

26:28.633 --> 26:30.000
Hello?

26:33.133 --> 26:34.567
[MOANING]

26:34.600 --> 26:36.200
[GROWLING]

26:37.800 --> 26:39.333
Hello?

26:42.667 --> 26:44.133
Who's there?

26:52.267 --> 26:53.467
Hello?

26:55.633 --> 26:56.700
Who's there?

26:56.733 --> 26:58.567
[GROWLING]

27:41.567 --> 27:43.533
[GROWLING]

27:49.667 --> 27:51.533
Hello?

27:52.633 --> 27:53.700
Hello?

28:15.100 --> 28:16.533
[GROWLING]

28:16.567 --> 28:18.467
[SHOUTING]

28:25.533 --> 28:26.533
Jerry?

28:47.800 --> 28:49.100
[KNOCKING]

28:49.667 --> 28:51.267
Hey, Ben.

28:51.300 --> 28:52.633
Angela.

28:52.667 --> 28:54.467
Sorry it took me
so long to visit.

28:54.500 --> 28:57.667
I just, um, I just needed
some time to clear up my head.

28:57.700 --> 28:59.367
I brought you some flowers.

28:59.400 --> 29:02.167
Make this place a little homier.

29:02.200 --> 29:03.467
Thank you.

29:11.233 --> 29:16.800
Ben, I, um, oh, I wish
Mom was still around.

29:16.833 --> 29:20.467
Me, too, of course.

29:20.500 --> 29:24.533
You were, um, you were way to
young to remember any of this,

29:24.567 --> 29:28.667
but, um, when we
were little, we were

29:28.700 --> 29:31.500
swimming in Uncle Frank's pool.

29:31.533 --> 29:36.267
You were just learning to walk,
and Uncle Frank was cooking.

29:36.300 --> 29:39.533
And he burned his
hand on the grill,

29:39.567 --> 29:44.167
and Mom went into the house to
get him some ice or something.

29:44.200 --> 29:47.467
Um, she was gone for
maybe 10 seconds,

29:47.500 --> 29:53.067
but that was all the time
it took you to fall in.

29:53.100 --> 29:57.567
I was the only one in the pool,
so I... I tried to save you,

29:57.600 --> 30:00.500
Ben.

30:00.533 --> 30:03.667
I just wasn't strong enough.

30:03.700 --> 30:08.533
I felt so alone and
just helpless, you know?

30:11.767 --> 30:18.533
I mean, Mom... Mom pulled us
out, but right now, Ben, right
now,

30:18.567 --> 30:24.433
I... I feel so
helpless and alone.

30:24.467 --> 30:26.633
And Mom's not here
to pull us out.

30:26.667 --> 30:31.067
Angela, we're fine.

30:31.100 --> 30:35.533
You... you honestly don't
have to worry about me.

30:35.567 --> 30:39.100
Oh, Ben, you
don't look so good.

30:48.400 --> 30:49.533
I'm going to go
talk to the doctors.

30:49.567 --> 30:50.733
You don't have to do that.

30:50.767 --> 30:52.367
You know what they're gonna say.

30:52.400 --> 30:54.133
I'll be back.

31:00.333 --> 31:02.667
[MUSIC PLAYING]

31:14.467 --> 31:17.033
[MUSIC STOPS]

31:26.300 --> 31:27.367
Hey.

31:27.400 --> 31:29.367
[HONKING]

31:30.333 --> 31:31.367
Come on.

31:32.067 --> 31:33.600
[GROWLING]
[SHOUTING]

31:44.433 --> 31:46.400
What the hell?

31:50.533 --> 31:53.100
[SPEAKING SPANISH ON TELEVISION]

32:02.133 --> 32:04.067
[GROANING IN PAIN]

32:13.200 --> 32:15.700
[SHOUTING]

32:56.200 --> 32:57.233
[SIGHING]

33:10.067 --> 33:11.200
[KNOCKING]

33:24.633 --> 33:27.267
Well, thank you for
coming, but you didn't
have to come all this way.

33:35.400 --> 33:36.433
Jerry?

34:11.766 --> 34:14.467
Oh, I think I already have.

34:14.500 --> 34:16.400
I mean, I've gotten better
at a lot of different things.

34:42.266 --> 34:43.699
Thank you for the cookies.

34:54.333 --> 34:55.367
[SNAPPING]

34:56.333 --> 34:58.267
[SNARLING]

35:06.367 --> 35:09.433
Se単ora, Se単ora!

35:10.767 --> 35:13.067
Oh, fuck, do you
want some of this?

35:50.300 --> 35:51.400
No, no, no.

35:55.400 --> 35:57.233
No, no, no, no, no.

36:02.700 --> 36:04.300
[ANGRY SHOUTING]

36:16.567 --> 36:19.233
[PHONE RINGING]

36:53.733 --> 36:55.533
It's you little bastards
doing this to me.

36:55.567 --> 36:57.133
I know it.

37:06.500 --> 37:09.000
[MUSIC PLAYING]

37:46.633 --> 37:47.767
[MUSIC STOPS]

37:47.800 --> 37:49.767
Hey, Ben.

37:49.800 --> 37:52.567
Chente, where
did you come from?

37:52.600 --> 37:54.500
I heard that the medicine
wasn't working good,

37:54.533 --> 37:58.233
so I brought you some new
stuff, expensive stuff.

38:07.400 --> 38:08.600
Thanks.

38:39.800 --> 38:41.667
[SHOUTING IN PAIN]

38:48.433 --> 38:51.033
[SCREAMING]

39:04.267 --> 39:06.100
[SOBBING]

39:06.133 --> 39:07.400
Jerry.

39:09.233 --> 39:11.233
Jerry?

39:11.267 --> 39:13.133
You all right, man?

39:16.133 --> 39:17.567
Dude, you all right?

39:17.600 --> 39:20.233
Jerry?

39:20.267 --> 39:22.400
[SNARLING]

39:25.767 --> 39:27.733
[GURGLING]

39:53.700 --> 39:56.400
[SNARLING]

40:15.667 --> 40:17.667
[GROWLING]

40:20.733 --> 40:23.133
[MUSIC PLAYING]

40:56.233 --> 40:58.333
Happy birthday, Ben.

41:17.833 --> 41:20.533
[GASPING]

41:55.067 --> 41:57.167
Ben.

41:57.200 --> 41:59.167
Angela?

41:59.200 --> 42:00.467
Angela.

42:02.833 --> 42:04.633
I know I said I
was feeling fine,

42:04.667 --> 42:07.500
but there is some serious
shit going on here.

42:09.700 --> 42:12.100
Angela, are you OK?

42:12.133 --> 42:16.433
Ben, I, uh, I... I
don't know what to do.

42:16.467 --> 42:18.567
The... the bills, they're...
they're stacking up.

42:18.600 --> 42:22.400
Chente, he feels horrible
about what happened.

42:22.433 --> 42:24.433
I... he stopped working, Ben.

42:24.467 --> 42:27.100
He's not going to work anymore.

42:27.133 --> 42:28.367
I... I... I don't
know what to do.

42:28.400 --> 42:31.033
I just... I... I don't
know what to do.

42:31.067 --> 42:35.467
I... I... I don't think I
can do this anymore, Ben.

42:35.500 --> 42:38.567
Just tell me what you want
me to do, and I'll do it.

42:38.600 --> 42:41.167
I just want you
to wake up, Ben.

42:41.200 --> 42:42.633
Just wake up.

42:42.667 --> 42:44.100
Ben!

42:44.133 --> 42:45.800
Wake up!

42:45.833 --> 42:47.100
Ben, just wake up.

42:47.133 --> 42:48.600
Wake up.

42:48.633 --> 42:49.767
Wake up.

42:49.800 --> 42:51.233
Ben!

42:53.633 --> 42:55.000
Wake up.

43:00.667 --> 43:02.667
[GASPING]

43:10.800 --> 43:13.233
I have your medicine.

43:13.267 --> 43:16.367
Ben, I don't know what to say.

43:16.400 --> 43:19.500
You can't know how
terrible I feel.

43:19.533 --> 43:23.033
Hey, Ben, sorry it took
me so long to stop by.

43:23.067 --> 43:25.467
I, uh, brought
you these flowers.

43:25.500 --> 43:27.533
Make this place a
little homier.

43:32.567 --> 43:33.767
[SHOUTING]

43:33.800 --> 43:34.667
No.

43:35.133 --> 43:36.700
No.

43:47.800 --> 43:50.000
[SINGING HAPPY BIRTHDAY
IN SPANISH]

43:59.500 --> 44:00.767
Happy birthday, Ben.

44:15.533 --> 44:17.600
Well done, Bennie.

44:17.633 --> 44:19.667
I thought I was going to
lose you there for a minute.

44:23.167 --> 44:24.100
Hmm.

44:24.133 --> 44:26.067
[ANGRY SHOUTING]

44:26.100 --> 44:27.800
Who the hell are you?

44:27.833 --> 44:31.100
Such hostility, Bennie.

44:31.133 --> 44:32.733
Oh, your father would
be so proud of you.

44:32.767 --> 44:34.567
[CHUCKLING]

44:35.467 --> 44:37.200
What did you say?

44:40.733 --> 44:44.267
Black, it's so hard
to keep clean, Bennie.

44:50.267 --> 44:51.367
How do I get out of here?

44:51.400 --> 44:53.600
Simple, you leave.

44:53.633 --> 44:55.467
How?

44:55.500 --> 44:58.100
You're asking me how to
leave a place that you built?

45:01.267 --> 45:04.300
What do you mean, a
place that I built?

45:04.333 --> 45:05.700
Look, Bennie, I... I
think we're getting ahead

45:05.733 --> 45:07.433
of ourselves a little bit here.

45:07.467 --> 45:09.200
Let's take it back
a couple days.

45:23.467 --> 45:25.433
OK, when did things
start getting...

45:25.467 --> 45:29.200
how should I put this... weird?

45:29.233 --> 45:31.767
What is all of this?

45:31.800 --> 45:35.333
Well, everything you
perceive as your reality

45:35.367 --> 45:39.100
really is your reality.

45:39.133 --> 45:45.633
OK, all of this, it's kind of
like falling asleep
with the TV on.

45:45.667 --> 45:48.667
You're just painting these
pictures with your mind,

45:48.700 --> 45:52.100
based on what you hear around
you... the conversations when

45:52.133 --> 45:54.367
people come to visit you, the
sounds of the man screaming

45:54.400 --> 45:56.500
in the bed next to you.

45:56.533 --> 46:00.367
Rargh, you get the idea, Bennie.

46:00.400 --> 46:02.667
You see.

46:02.700 --> 46:07.300
I really can be helpful if you
let me, but here's the thing.

46:07.333 --> 46:09.267
People will go on
with their lives.

46:09.300 --> 46:13.400
Bills will be paid,
and love will be made.

46:13.433 --> 46:15.267
Meanwhile, everyone
forgets all about little

46:15.300 --> 46:17.667
Bennie and the bump on his head.

46:32.833 --> 46:34.667
They always forget, Bennie.

46:39.700 --> 46:42.633
Then what am I supposed to do?

46:42.667 --> 46:45.633
Everything that exists
here is inside of you.

46:45.667 --> 46:47.633
You've just ignored it for so
long that what happens here,

46:47.667 --> 46:50.467
it feels like someone
else's nightmare,

46:50.500 --> 46:53.467
but this is your
nightmare, Bennie.

46:53.500 --> 46:56.333
There are no outside
elements, only what

46:56.367 --> 46:59.400
you observe those
elements to be.

46:59.433 --> 47:01.500
The sooner you accept
that, the sooner

47:01.533 --> 47:03.033
you can wake yourself up.

47:09.267 --> 47:13.033
Who the hell are you?

47:13.067 --> 47:16.033
Well, I'm everything
you've ever read,

47:16.067 --> 47:18.700
everything you've ever
seen, touched, tasted,

47:18.733 --> 47:19.800
heard, or learned.

47:19.833 --> 47:22.333
That, Bennie, is who I am.

47:27.100 --> 47:30.267
No, buddy, a freaking
whack job is who you are.

47:36.533 --> 47:39.533
Doctora, Doctora!

47:39.567 --> 47:41.733
Why do I have a feeling
that doesn't lead to heaven?

49:00.400 --> 49:02.300
What is this?

49:02.767 --> 49:04.767
Your way home.

49:06.533 --> 49:07.800
Look.
You don't understand.

49:07.833 --> 49:10.100
If you...

49:10.133 --> 49:11.467
[SHOUTING IN PAIN]

49:14.067 --> 49:16.133
[SOBBING]

49:18.300 --> 49:20.233
Help me, please.

49:20.267 --> 49:21.533
No, please.

49:21.567 --> 49:23.233
[SHOUTING]

49:29.200 --> 49:30.733
Damn it, Bennie.

49:30.767 --> 49:32.600
I didn't want this for you.

49:32.633 --> 49:35.433
Your mother is a lying whore.

49:35.467 --> 49:36.667
I'm the innocent one.

49:36.700 --> 49:38.467
Please, stop!

49:40.467 --> 49:43.000
[SOBBING]

50:29.533 --> 50:31.233
Please, no, please.

50:31.267 --> 50:32.367
I'm sorry.

50:32.400 --> 50:34.667
[SOBBING]

50:53.733 --> 50:54.800
[GUNSHOT]

50:54.833 --> 50:56.367
[SHOUTING]

50:58.200 --> 51:00.033
You haven't thought
of this in a long time.

51:00.067 --> 51:02.100
Why would I want to?

51:02.133 --> 51:05.333
You can't pretend it
didn't happen, Bennie.

51:05.367 --> 51:07.633
Don't give me that bullshit.

51:07.667 --> 51:09.500
It's your fear that
makes him strong.

51:09.533 --> 51:12.533
It's like a darkness
that infects you.

51:12.567 --> 51:14.100
You confronted him once.

51:14.133 --> 51:16.433
And for what?

51:16.467 --> 51:18.767
A dead mother and
a damaged head.

51:22.133 --> 51:24.067
How do I get out of here?

51:24.100 --> 51:27.667
This is yours to control.

51:44.300 --> 51:46.633
Screw this.

51:46.667 --> 51:49.333
[SNARLING]

51:52.433 --> 51:53.633
Piss off!

51:54.700 --> 51:57.100
[MOANING]

52:19.133 --> 52:21.133
Mine to control.

52:24.233 --> 52:26.467
[FOOTSTEPS]

52:28.333 --> 52:30.533
[KNOCKING]

52:34.067 --> 52:36.400
Ben, bro...

52:38.533 --> 52:43.267
Long time.
I... I'm sorry, bro.

52:43.300 --> 52:46.133
You know, when I
lost my job, I...

52:46.167 --> 52:49.500
I just feel like I needed
to get away, you know?

52:49.533 --> 52:54.700
Um, I've been a bad friend.

52:54.733 --> 52:57.333
Here you are, lying
in bed, while I'm

52:57.367 --> 52:59.267
up north, smoking weed.

53:07.467 --> 53:10.567
It's good to see you, Jerry.

53:10.600 --> 53:14.233
It's good to see you, Ben.

53:14.267 --> 53:15.533
What do we do now?

53:20.533 --> 53:23.200
[MUSIC PLAYING]

54:04.533 --> 54:09.333
Whoa, what have we
got here, brother?

54:09.367 --> 54:12.267
No.

54:12.300 --> 54:14.033
That's a pretty lady.

54:14.067 --> 54:17.633
Jerry, stay in the car.

54:17.667 --> 54:19.733
Oh, don't worry.
I'm gonna stay right here.

54:19.767 --> 54:21.567
You got this, bro.

54:21.600 --> 54:26.200
No, no.
No. No!

54:29.667 --> 54:31.133
Hey!

55:18.633 --> 55:20.233
Se単orita.

55:28.733 --> 55:30.533
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

55:37.400 --> 55:40.400
Yes, I am now.

55:52.800 --> 55:55.300
I didn't get your name.

55:55.333 --> 55:59.700
Ben, and yours?

55:59.733 --> 56:02.300
You don't know who I am?

56:02.333 --> 56:05.167
No, ma'am, I don't.

56:05.200 --> 56:10.633
I am Jubilee, and
I'm not a ma'am.

56:10.667 --> 56:12.767
Well, all right.

56:12.800 --> 56:15.167
[HUMMING]

56:21.667 --> 56:22.767
Jerry.

56:22.800 --> 56:24.133
Yes?

56:24.167 --> 56:25.567
This is Jubilee.

56:25.600 --> 56:27.200
Hi, Jerry.

56:28.733 --> 56:32.200
Oh, my.

56:32.233 --> 56:35.333
Hi, Jubilee.

56:35.367 --> 56:38.033
Listen, man, we're gonna
be giving her a ride home.
You want to hop in the back?

56:38.067 --> 56:39.533
Yeah, yeah.

56:49.167 --> 56:52.633
Hey, I'm here in
town for a while.

56:52.667 --> 56:56.467
I'm actually an actress,
and I'm filming a movie.

56:56.500 --> 56:58.633
An actress?

56:58.667 --> 57:01.667
Well, sorta, I
mean, no one knows

57:01.700 --> 57:04.567
who I am outside Latin America,
but even a Mexican movie

57:04.600 --> 57:07.467
is something to see.

57:07.500 --> 57:09.100
We're filming tomorrow
in the park downtown.

57:09.133 --> 57:10.600
Do you know it?

57:10.633 --> 57:13.200
we start at 8 in
the morning, but don't

57:13.233 --> 57:15.533
come until 10 or so.

57:15.567 --> 57:18.633
Nothing interesting
happens until then.

57:18.667 --> 57:20.300
OK.

57:35.533 --> 57:37.600
Shit.

57:37.633 --> 57:39.400
What are you doing?

57:41.600 --> 57:43.000
[SNAP]

57:43.467 --> 57:45.033
Still here.

57:50.133 --> 57:51.333
Bennie, uh, ju... just stop.

57:51.367 --> 57:53.133
You're... you're wasting time.

57:55.567 --> 57:57.167
You said this world
was mine to control.

57:57.200 --> 57:59.067
I want you gone.

57:59.100 --> 58:00.100
I'm an exception.

58:00.133 --> 58:03.033
I'm part of you.

58:03.067 --> 58:04.500
Whatever, man.

58:04.533 --> 58:06.167
Have you even considered trying
to get out of the situation

58:06.200 --> 58:08.433
that you're in?

58:08.467 --> 58:10.100
I've been busy.

58:10.133 --> 58:14.500
Yeah, busy, playing Jackie Chan
and manufacturing a new car.

58:14.533 --> 58:16.033
I hate the bus.

58:16.067 --> 58:19.233
And now a dream girl?

58:19.267 --> 58:20.667
What's wrong with any of that?

58:20.700 --> 58:23.367
You think she would ever
actually talk to you?

58:23.400 --> 58:26.167
This whole thing is a big soap
opera you're trying to produce.

58:26.200 --> 58:28.200
You said I had free reign here.

58:28.233 --> 58:30.467
I never said that.

58:30.500 --> 58:31.633
Look.

58:31.667 --> 58:35.433
Just... will you just let
me enjoy this for a second?

58:35.467 --> 58:38.033
In this world, a
second, it could

58:38.067 --> 58:40.133
be a minute in the real world.

58:40.167 --> 58:42.667
An hour could be a day,
sometimes a week, depending,

58:42.700 --> 58:45.133
and the farther you
get into this world,

58:45.167 --> 58:47.567
the harder it is to
get out, the easier it

58:47.600 --> 58:48.900
is to forget about
little Bennie.

58:52.767 --> 58:54.567
Don't worry about it, boss.

58:54.600 --> 58:57.500
I got it covered.

58:57.533 --> 58:59.400
And cut the Bennie shit.

01:00:07.433 --> 01:00:09.733
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:01:30.300 --> 01:01:34.100
At Christmas, my mom will
make our neighbor dress up

01:01:34.133 --> 01:01:37.233
like Santa Claus...
him or Elvis.

01:01:37.267 --> 01:01:39.233
Really?

01:01:39.267 --> 01:01:44.267
And one time, my mom had our
neighbor dress up like Elvis,

01:01:44.300 --> 01:01:47.167
dressed up as Santa.

01:01:47.200 --> 01:01:50.633
A Santa Elvis impersonator?

01:01:50.667 --> 01:01:53.467
An ideal man, what can I say?

01:02:06.400 --> 01:02:10.633
So the movie shooting
seems like it's going well.

01:02:10.667 --> 01:02:14.800
I have something that I've
been putting off telling you.

01:02:14.833 --> 01:02:17.700
Tomorrow is the last day.

01:02:17.733 --> 01:02:19.333
What?

01:02:20.133 --> 01:02:22.600
I should have said something.

01:02:22.633 --> 01:02:25.300
It's just that I've been
having such a great time

01:02:25.333 --> 01:02:28.033
with you, and...

01:02:28.067 --> 01:02:30.267
Then what?

01:02:30.300 --> 01:02:32.433
I don't know.

01:02:32.467 --> 01:02:37.633
I guess I will go
back to Mexico City,

01:02:37.667 --> 01:02:44.600
or maybe I will hang out
here a couple more days.

01:02:46.200 --> 01:02:48.700
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:03:25.533 --> 01:03:27.800
So I was thinking
about your offer

01:03:27.833 --> 01:03:30.700
the other night, about staying
around a couple of days

01:03:30.733 --> 01:03:35.367
after you finish shooting,
and I thought that maybe we

01:03:35.400 --> 01:03:38.600
could get away for a couple
of days, maybe go to the beach

01:03:38.633 --> 01:03:41.367
and get some rest.

01:03:41.400 --> 01:03:44.533
Seth called me this morning.

01:03:44.567 --> 01:03:46.300
I got an offer to
do another movie.

01:03:46.333 --> 01:03:49.467
That's great.

01:03:49.500 --> 01:03:55.167
In London, it's the
role of a lifetime, Ben.

